An aunt who inserted a stick in the genitals of 12-year-old Igho Osegbe has been remanded at the Sapele Correctional facility in Delta state Mercy Oba, 35, assaulted her niece for “stealing” her garri and fish last Thursday at Ikumeje-Okpara Inland in the Ethiope East council area. Oba was arraigned at the Magistrate Court II, Isiokolo on Monday. She is facing a four-count charge of assault, infliction of bodily harm on the child and her visually impaired mother as well as destruction of their properties worth N200,000. Parts of the charge reads: “That you Mercy Oba ‘f’ on the 17th day of March 2022 at Ikumeje village, Okpara Inland within Isiokolo Magistrate District did assault one Igho Osegbe ‘f’ by beating her and thereby committed an offence punishable under section351 of the Criminal Code cap C21 Vol. 1 Laws of Delta State of Nigeria 2006.   Security agents barricade Cross River Assembly over sack of…     2023: Saraki picks PDP presidential nomination form     Bamise: Lagos BRT driver remanded over alleged rape, murder   “That you Mercy Oba ‘f’ on the said date and at the aforementioned magistrate district did cause grievous harm to one Igho Osegbe ‘f’ by robbing pepper all over her body and inserting a stick into her vagina and thereby committed an offence punishable under section 335 of the criminal code, cap 21 Vol 1… “That you Mercy Oba f on the 17th day of March 2022 did assault one Odiri Oba ‘f’ by beating and hitting her on the ground and thereby committed an offence punishable under section 351 of the criminal code, cap 21, vol 1… “That you Mercy Oba did willfully and unlawfully damaged or destroyed bed, stove, plates and other household items valued N200,000 properties of one Odiri Oba and thereby committed an offence punishable under section 451 of the criminal code 21 vol 1…” The case was adjourned to March 30.